# Expo App Styling: NativeWind

- **All UI styling** in `sunnahsleep-expo` must use **NativeWind**: use `className` with Tailwind-style classes on React Native components (e.g. `View`, `Text`, `Pressable`).
- **Do not** use `StyleSheet.create()` or inline `style={{}}` for layout, spacing, colors, or typography. Use `className` instead so the app stays consistent with Tailwind and looks good.
- Example: `<View className="flex-1 bg-background p-4"><Text className="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground">Title</Text></View>`
- Ensure `tailwind.config.js`, `global.css`, and Metro/Babel are configured for NativeWind per official docs. Design tokens (colors, spacing) should align with the PWA where possible.
